neighbors.name: Mary Harper Dake
neighbors.claims: Mary Harper Dake owns property in Orleans Parish but has no evident public presence in local civic affairs ([wwwcfprd.doa.louisiana.gov](https://wwwcfprd.doa.louisiana.gov/boardsandcommissions/viewContacts.cfm?board=239#:~:text=East%20New%20Orleans%20Neighborhood%20Advisory,5949%20%7C%20enonac2009%40gmail.com)). No meeting minutes or news reports were found that mention her involvement in community or development issues ([wwwcfprd.doa.louisiana.gov](https://wwwcfprd.doa.louisiana.gov/boardsandcommissions/viewContacts.cfm?board=239#:~:text=East%20New%20Orleans%20Neighborhood%20Advisory,5949%20%7C%20enonac2009%40gmail.com)).

approach_recommendations.engage: Reach out in a personal, respectful way emphasizing minimal disruption to her home life and property value stability.

neighbors.name: Luis A. Quijosaca-Agualsaca
neighbors.claims: Luis A. Quijosaca-Agualsaca is listed as a property owner in Orleans Parish, but he has no identifiable footprint in local news or public records ([www.wwno.org](https://www.wwno.org/wwno/2025-05-13/new-orleans-historian-on-tracing-pope-leo-xivs-hidden-creole-roots#:~:text=WWNO%20www,New%20OrleansPope%20Leo%20XIVcatholic%20church)). There are no public statements or civic roles on record under his name in the New Orleans area ([www.wwno.org](https://www.wwno.org/wwno/2025-05-13/new-orleans-historian-on-tracing-pope-leo-xivs-hidden-creole-roots#:~:text=WWNO%20www,New%20OrleansPope%20Leo%20XIVcatholic%20church)).

approach_recommendations.engage: Provide project details in plain language (and Spanish if needed), stressing safety measures and that local property values and street safety will be protected.

neighbors.name: Charles L. Green
neighbors.claims: Charles L. Green was a lifelong resident of Algiers in Orleans Parish ([www.davismortuaryservice.com](https://www.davismortuaryservice.com/obituaries/5966442#:~:text=Charles%20,Beloved)). He served as a Social Studies teacher with the Orleans Parish school system for 34 years and was a U.S. Army Reserve Master Sergeant ([www.davismortuaryservice.com](https://www.davismortuaryservice.com/obituaries/5966442#:~:text=Friday%2C%20May%2015%2C%202015%20at,Brother%20of%20Geraldine%20G)). No evidence was found of him taking a public stand on development or clean energy in local forums (he is not recorded speaking in city meetings or media on such issues) ([www.legacy.com](https://www.legacy.com/us/obituaries/nola/name/charles-green-obituary?id=33249863#:~:text=Charles%20Green%20Obituary)) ([www.legacy.com](https://www.legacy.com/us/obituaries/nola/name/charles-green-obituary?id=33249863#:~:text=late%20Rev,and)).

approach_recommendations.engage: Connect through a community figure (e.g., a local veteran or educator) who knows him, highlighting how the project honors the neighborhood’s character and quiet.

overview_summary: All three profiled neighbors have no clear public stance on development, and none are known to have taken outspoken positions on local projects. Influence levels are generally low, with no current officeholders or major community leaders among them, though one neighbor had long community ties as an educator.
